     Just @{"Install" link installation} it and run it from /X or S!X.

  Then you can type "Z HELP" or "Z ?" if you should ever wonder how it works.




                         About the Dirlist operators :
             <Ŧ=-----------------------------------------------ŧ>

 
  You may use any of these syntax : 1,2,3-6,u,a 

  A = ALL directories. When encountered this letter in a dirlist, all dirs will
      automaticly be searched through. Even if you have specified dirnr infront
      of this argument.

  U = Upload dir. Usually the last directory of your conference DirX structure.

  , = Seperator. Used to choose multiple dirnr. to check through. 1,2,3,4..etc.

  - = Mark dirs. Handy when you wish to search through dirs 1 => 7.. "1-7" will
      then be the correct syntax. Can be combined with seperator. 


      For instant : Z 1,4-7,12-22 my-search-words..

      (or like this: Z my-search-words.. 1,4-7,12-22 ... The same thing! :)





                       About the Searchlist operators :
             <Ŧ=----------------------------------------------ŧ>

  You may use any of these syntax : &, !, / 

  & = logic AND of searchwords. For instant, you wish to find a file_id which
      contains both the word "Amiga_News" AND "#14" ... Then you can simply
      write : Z a Amiga_news & #14   ... and you would skip all the other files
      that doesn't have BOTH these words in the File_id... VERY useful when
      searching for a specified disk-nr. in a diskset for a program.

  ! = logic NOT. This is used the same way as the &, but often combined with
      the & operator. Example : Z a Amiga_news &! #14 ! Lizard

  / = Is used to find a file_id with none of the above operators involved.
      For instant : Z a lizard & instant / magz

      This would lead to a search after the two words "lizard" AND "instant",
      or a file_id with only the word "magz" in.  



  REMEMBER : The search-string is NON-CASE-SENSITIVE... To easy your pain! :)



  The Searchlist options will ONLY be available in the REGISTERED versions. 
    Do consider to register your door. You'll then be able to recieve the 
                           future upgrades for FREE.


